JOHANNESBURG - The South African Football Association has announced Hugo Broos as the new Bafana Bafana coach on Wednesday. The Belgian national takes over from Molefi Ntseki. Broos coached Cameroon between 2016-17, winning the Afcon Championship in 2017. READ: Safa receives 200 applications for Bafana head coach His appointment follows weeks of postponement by Safa, who’ve been scrambling to secure the services of a new coach. The 69-year-old replaces Ntseki, who was relieved of his duties a little over a month ago. Ntseki failed to qualify for the Africa Cup of Nations taking place in Cameroon.